The '''Melikian-Ouzounian School''', established in 1921, was the first [[Armenia]]n School in [[Cyprus]]. It was named after two prominent families, [[Melikian]] and [[Ouzounian]]. Education was closely linked to the [[Armenian Church]] [[Notre Dame de Tyre]]. In 1963, the Melikian-Ouzounian School was taken over by the [[Turkish people|Turks]] after inter-communal fighting between the [[Greek Cypriots]] and [[Turkish Cypriots]].<ref>https://www.scribd.com/doc/21770562/The-Armenians-of-Cyprus</ref>

