[[File:Monuments_Men_Foundation_logo.jpg|thumb|Monuments Men Foundation logo]]
The '''Monuments Men Foundation for the Preservation of Art''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Foundation (nonprofit organization)|foundation]], which honors the legacy of the men and women who served in the [[Monuments, Fine Arts, and Archives program]] (known as the "Monuments Men")<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.monumentsmenfoundation.org/about/ |title=Monuments Men Foundation For the Preservation of Art – About The Foundation |accessdate=2008-02-07}}</ref> during and after [[World War II]]. Their heroic work of protecting and safeguarding civilization’s most important artistic and cultural treasures from armed conflict is unprecedented.{{Citation needed|date=October 2018}}
It was founded in 2007<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neh.gov/about/awards/national-humanities-medals/monuments-men-foundation-preservation-art|title=Awards & Honors: National Humanities Medals - National Endowment for the Humanities|website=www.neh.gov}}</ref> by [[Robert M. Edsel]], author of ''[[Rescuing Da Vinci]]'', ''The Monuments Men: Allied Heroes, Nazi Thieves and the Greatest Treasure Hunt in History'', and ''Saving Italy: The Race to Rescue a Nation's Treasures from the Nazis''. Raising public awareness is essential to the Foundation’s mission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monumentsmenfoundation.org/about-the-foundation|title=About the Foundation - Monuments Men Foundation|website=www.monumentsmenfoundation.org}}</ref>
The Monuments Men Foundation is one of the recipients of the 2007 [[National Humanities Medal]]s.<ref> "6 Academics Receive National Honors in Arts and Humanities" Chronicle of Higher Education Nov. 16, 2007 [http://chronicle.com/daily/2007/11/733n.htm?at summary]</ref> The award cited it for "sustained efforts to recognize the contributions of the scholar-soldiers of the Second World War."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neh.gov/news/archive/20071115.html|title=News Archive - National Endowment for the Humanities|website=www.neh.gov}}</ref>
