'''Preservation administrators''' are librarians who are trained in the management of [[Preservation (library and archival science)|preservation]] in libraries and archives. The term is often used as a parallel term to [[Conservator-restorer|conservator]], an allied profession that is focused primarily on the corrective repair of artefacts. The term "preservationist" has fairly wide usage as a synonym for "preservation administrator" or a broader term for anyone active in the fields of conservation or preservation, but has never found professional favor.
